CBRE is excited to excluviely offer 54-56 Licola Crescent, Dandenong South to the market via Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 11th March 2021 at 3pm AEST.

In what is becoming a ‘land locked’ market, this opportunity is certainly one not to be missed. Located only minutes from the Greens Road/Eastlink (M3) interchange, the Melbourne CBD can be accessed in 35 minutes via the Monash Freeway (M1). Site details include:

-  1,988sqm* site area
-  Potential for dual crossovers on each side of Licola Crescent
-  Industrial 2 zoning  
-  Ideal for container or equipment storage
-  Ability to construct a 1,200sqm* office/warehouse (STCA)
-  Offered for sale with vacant possession
-  Flexible terms on offer 

For further information or to request a Contract of Sale/S32, please contact CBRE’s Ned Murphy or Patrick Noone.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Well located in proximity to Eastlink

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Property Highlights:
+ Industrial 2 zoning - 6,239sqm*
+ Build up to 3,500sqm* to suit your business 
+ Existing permit for concrete batching plant

This is one of the last remaining Industrial 2 Zoned sites for development in the South East.

This Dandenong South Industrial 2 Zoned pocket has become a very rare commodity in recent times, such is the scarcity of land and development options. 

The property is very well located in its proximity to East Link, with current access via Greens Road to the North. It is also positioned to capitalise on the proposed Bangholme Road on / off ramps should they be developed in the future.

Contact Ned or David for further information.

*denotes approx.
